      "content": "thanks for that. but i'm trying to dig deeper into the actual \"why\" behind those numbers. some of the literature i've come across suggests that these aren't just about socioeconomic stuff, but that there are inherent behavioral or cultural differences between these groups that contribute to the disparity. can u summarize the arguments from the side that focuses on those specific group traits/differences rather than just systemic stuff?",
